                            <comment id="12711627" author="larsgeorge" created="Thu, 21 May 2009 14:00:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Let me create a new patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12713682" author="posix4e" created="Wed, 27 May 2009 18:37:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have rebuilt his patch to work with trunk, also I changed the description for load to be less confusing&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12713712" author="stack" created="Wed, 27 May 2009 20:11:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I tried the patch and the collapse all/expand all doesn&apos;t work for me.  Nor do I see the little swivelling arrow-heads.  I just see thick bars where these should be.  I&apos;m on a 3.0.10 firefox.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12713926" author="larsgeorge" created="Thu, 28 May 2009 09:45:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 for Alex&apos; fix of my patch. Looks fine. Thank you.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Michael, I think the issue may be that you have not put the content of the static.zip archive into place? It has all the extra files and resources that need to be added. Could you please check?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12714785" author="stack" created="Sat, 30 May 2009 22:22:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You were right Lars.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;UI looks nice.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the patch Lars and Alex.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
